	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Dec 11th 3:09 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.37]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The SK epic is HARDLY pathetic and I know not why people frequently claim that it is.&nbsp;&nbsp;It has to be one of the most underrated weapons in the game.<br><br>Few argue the buffs that it gives, as they are pretty good (granted, I would really love to see a STA buff on there, but...).  And the ratio, while not great, is still respectable.<br><br>The primary reason that Inn Curse is so powerful is due to its proc.  A 250 lifetap DoT over 30 secs equates to a 8.33 DPS, and, oh by the way, you are getting healed for that amount also.  That DPS is almost the equivalant of a WAR wielding a lammy in his offhand.  Run the numbers for DPS.  They quickly show that Inn Curse, on the proc, will outdamage all but the most powerful weapons in the game and this is a Kunark item.<br><br>Many like to argue that you cant rely on the proc, as its unpredicatable.  I just dont see the logic in that argument.  It IS going to proc; that is a fact.  How can you just ignore it all together?  Probably the best way to evaluate procs is over time.  For instance, weapon &quot;X&quot; procs &quot;Y&quot; number of times over &quot;Z&quot; time interval.  That might make sense.  But to ignore the proc altogether is just plain silly.<br><br>I am the first to admit that nowadays, the &quot;cost&quot; of getting Inn Curse doesnt necessarily justify the benefit of it.  Its essentially an outdated item.  But that doesnt mean that if you already have it that it doesnt perform well.  <br><br>Luna<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
