	   <tr><td colspan=2>Your message suggests that a paladin or an enchanter is an easier fight than a NEC.&nbsp;&nbsp;Sorry, but I strongly disagree.<br><br>A PLD, like an SK, is a very tough PvP fight and a ENC is not that much easier, if at all.  Both can stand up very well against an SK.  I would choose to PvP a NEC every day before I opted to get into it with a PLD or a ENC.<br><br>Regarding PvP a NEC, I would never waste my time and try and kill the NECs pet.  That would be pretty much be exactly what he would want you to do.  You must deny him that luxury.  See my message below for possible tactics.<br><br>A NEC is not going to be able to stand in front of a SK for very long before he gets to 40%ish health (around this time, a nice HT will give him lots of trouble, if not kill him outright).  A NEC cant cast if he's running.  Therefore, he needs to be prepared for when the SK charges him, because he should know that a &quot;banzai!&quot; attack is going to come.  Some of his choices are snare or SS away from you.  If he doesnt have either of those up, the SK is going to have a huge advantage.  Dealing the NEC pet is fairly easy and he wont have much of a defense without his pet drawing your attention or either of those spells.<br><br>A ENC is not exactly fun either.  If the SK doesnt kill him quick, you are going to get the tar &quot;sapped&quot; out of you and are probably in for a long fight.  Its actually pretty funny.  Tash comes, stun comes, mana sieve comes, the whole nine yards.  What was once a mighty SK quickly gets transformed into a fledgling WAR....<br><br>I dont even want to get into it with a PLD either.  Talk about a pain in the butt fight.  They can melee well, I hate their fast casting heals (in PvP that is), and LoH is a fight turning ability.  Cast and used at the proper time, its almost akin to killing the tard twice.<br><br>You have fun dueling PLD and ENC.  You success rate will surely be lower than if you took on a NEC.  NECs are super characters and can do well in PvP, but I just think that ENC and PLD are just even more worrisome in PvP...possibly by a significant margin.<br><br>Luna<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
