	   <a name=103704250730606></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f103704250730606><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=103704250730606>RE: Trl Sk</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=103704250730606#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=145263><span id=Scholar>lunaticfringesk</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>262 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 11th 2:42 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Several schools of thought.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>At the end of the day, however, it really only boils down to putting points into 2 stats though, those being intelligence and stamina (for a Troll that is).<br><br>I suppose the first question I would ask myself is whether or not if I planned on taking this Troll SK to level 60-65 or not or if you believe that you will be much more a casual player.<br><br>If you do plan on taking him to 60-65, then there is an argument to put all the points into STA at creation, as it is generally more efficient to get mana from items at the &quot;end game&quot; than from INT (and there are plenty of direct mana items out there).<br><br>If you are a more casual player, then clearly you want to put some into INT, as like at lower levels will be much more challenging with such a tiny mana pool.<br><br>Therefore, I would pick one of the following:<br><br>If you are a casual player, then perhaps 10 STA and 10 INT would be the route I would go with.  Perhaps 15 INT and 5 STA might also work.<br><br>If you are a hardcore player and plan on hitting 60-65, then it is challenging to go wrong.  However, some would argue all 20 into STA is the way to go.<br><br>(If hardcore) Personally, I think that the above (10 STA, 10 INT) or even all 20 into INT could work also if you are a hardcore player.  Its hard to go wrong in that situation.<br><br>At the end game, however, I can assure you that STA is definitely the way to go and that that is one stat that you just cannot have enough of.<br><br>Luna<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
