	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Nov 12th 5:42 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>With that bankroll, I would not hesitate and go purchase an Ebon Mace.&nbsp;&nbsp;For a 1H weapon, that will be your primary one until you can upgrade to a Shard of Night (Massive Dragonclaw Shard is also a possibility, but is generally much more expensive).<br><br>As far as upgrading your 1HS, there isnt a ton to choose from.  Sword of Pain in Velks, as previously mentioned, is a good choice, as its better than Ebon Mace, but you cant purchase it.  If you wanted a 1HS now, Noct Blade would probably be the way to go, but I wouldnt take that over Ebon Mace anyways.  Massive Dragonclaw Shard is the only purchaseable 1HS that I can think of (pre-PoP that is) that would be better than Ebon Mace.  Shard of Night, however, is generally much cheaper and is essentially as good before lvl58, and is better 58+.  If you want to do a quest, Greenmist is better than Shard of Night.<br><br>To be honest, I wouldnt wield a 2HS (except for keeping the skill up, if desired) at level 50.  You are probably under the alleged ac softcap, so I would crank up ac as much as possible.  I can look into 2HS if desired, but I dont recommend it.<br><br>Hope this helps,<br><br>Luna<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
